# AISDLC-320: RFC-0024 Refit Phase 1 — draft captures are operator-local (OQ-1).
# Explicit submit (`cli-capture submit`) promotes to team-shared backlog/captures/.
.ai-sdlc/captures-drafts/
# AISDLC-133: per-task reviewer verdict files written by /ai-sdlc execute
# Step 10 and consumed by `.husky/pre-push` (scripts/check-attestation-sign.sh)
# to auto-sign the DSSE attestation. Ephemeral, per-worktree — never
# committed; the signed envelope at .ai-sdlc/attestations/<sha>.dsse.json is
# the durable artifact.
.ai-sdlc/verdicts/
# AISDLC-155: per-worktree active-task sentinel (AISDLC-81). The sentinel
# lives INSIDE each worktree at `<worktree>/.active-task` and is read by the
# PreToolUse hook to resolve which task's `permittedExternalPaths` apply for
# cross-repo writes. Ephemeral, per-worktree — never committed. Was tracked
# by accident in earlier commits and kept causing merge conflicts on every
# rebase as parallel worktrees each tried to write their own task ID.
.active-task
.enterprise.yaml

# AISDLC-122: pipeline-cli writes the DoR calibration log to
# `artifacts/_dor/calibration.jsonl` by default. The log captures issue
# titles + body previews + LLM-derived `finding` / `clarificationQuestion`
# strings that may quote pasted secrets. Combined with the dogfood
# pipeline's `git add -A` practice (per `feedback_stash_completely_before_pipelines.md`),
# an unscrubbed paste of an API key in an issue body could be committed
# to git history through this log. Three layers of defense:
#   1. Ignore the directory entirely (this rule).
#   2. Lower BODY_INLINE_LIMIT in pipeline-cli/src/dor/calibration-log.ts
#      (80 chars), so most bodies become a SHA reference.
#   3. Regex redaction in pipeline-cli/src/dor/secret-redact.ts.
artifacts/

